column5: Someone who needlessly fears the worst after using the internet to self-diagnose an ailment.
You got a problem with that Bubba?  Have you been hacking my puter???  Sometimes it's the only way some of us know what's wrong with us!!!
I would never have known about mycoplasma pneumonia or onchomycosis without the interweb.  Just because you might be a hypochondriac doesn't mean that you're not sick.
My favorite tombstone....."I told you I was sick!"

I think there is a cure for that but you may experience...excessive slobbering or dry mouth,in some rare cases high blood pressure may occur, or low blood pressure, you may experience high levels of hyperactivity or may cause drowsiness,may cause constipation,excessive diharrea, and gas with oily discharge
I hate me some oily discharge myself.
